@{
    ViewBag.Title = "New England Womens Hockey League";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}
@section headerPlugins
{

    <!-- jQuery (necessary for Bootstrap's JavaScript plugins) -->
    <script type="text/javascript" src="~/Scripts/jquery.min.js"></script>

    <!-- Include all compiled plugins (below), or include individual files as needed -->
    <script src="~/Scripts/bootstrap.min.js"></script>
}
<section class="main__middle__container">
    <div class="container recent-posts">
        <h2 class="text-center"><span>Our Programs</span></h2>
        <div class="row no_padding no-margin">
            <h3>C/D Level</h3>
            <hr>
            <p>Any player who plays hockey at D or C level is eligible for this program. Any player who plays hockey at D level is also eligible for the Recreational program on Tuesdays and Stickhandling/Shooting program on Thursdays. This program is designed for the faster-paced more competitive player. All aspects of hockey, including an emphasis on improving your conditioning, skating skills, stick handling, and game strategy will be taught by our knowledgeable instructors. </p>
            <p>The Skills Development Program for C and D level players consists of one 1.5 hr skill session per week on Wednesday 9:40 - 11:10, and one game per week on Friday. We also offer options that include Rec skill sessions on Tuesdays and stickhandling / shooting skills on Thursdays. For those of you who can’t get enough hockey, we also offer the option of Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday skills, and Friday games.</p>
            <p>Thursday's 9:30 - 11:00am Shooting and Stick Handling. This skills program is designed for players who are serious about taking their Shooting & Stickhandling abilities to the next level. Players will be instructed and shown good technique, going through quality repetitions and being provided with positive feedback thus enhancing their ability to succeed.</p>
            <p>Please note that Friday games are not a required element of this program. You can sign up for the skills only portion for the season.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <img src="~/Content/Images/content__images/Somerville.jpg" alt="image" class="img-responsive no-margin">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
                <h3>Schedule</h3>
                <hr>
                <p>The C/D Hockey Skills program is held on <strong>Wednesdays from 9:30 am to 11:00 am</strong></p>
                <p>The Stick Handling and Shooting program is held on <strong>Thursdays from 9:30 am to 11:00 am</strong></p>
                <p>Registration with USA Hockey is required to participate in any of our programs</p>
                <p>Equipment required: Hockey helmet with face guard, shin guards, hockey socks, elbow and shoulder pads, hockey gloves, hockey pants, hockey skates, stick, mouth guard and Big Water Bottle.</p>
                <p>All play is at Nashoba Valley Olympia, 34 Massachusetts Ave., Route 111, Boxborough, MA 01719</p>
                <p>
                    <a href="/Programs/Register" role="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Register Now</a>
                    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
                    <a href="/Programs/Schedule" role="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">See Full Schedule</a>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
